frus:attachment.p:
That, according to the provisions of the civil legislation of the Federal
                        District, all works constructed on lands of the public domain without due
                        authorization are the property of the nation by right of accession;

That even though contracts, concessions or permissions exist, they have
                        almost invariably been based upon favoritism or lucre, without the nation
                        deriving the benefit to which it has right;
